<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-11-21T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-11-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A16/76: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-21T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 21,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>260. For Wilson. Your despatch No. 609, October 2, concerning Arms
                            Manufacture Commission.<note n="70" xml:id="d264fn70">Not printed; see
                                telegram No. 92, Oct. 2, 3 p.m., from the Minister in Switzerland,
                                    <ref target="#pg_314">p. 314</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p>Department is sending by pouch to Berne two instructions (1) approving
                            your position at last session of Commission,<note n="71" xml:id="d264fn71"><hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> and (2)
                            designating you as American Delegate to attend Third Session.<note n="72" xml:id="d264fn72">Not printed.</note> Rand is being
                            instructed to act as Technical Assistant, and Blake as Disbursing
                            Officer.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>